[test symbolic.it]
# gen65 bilingual ratchet: register recognition is STRUCTURAL, not English
# lexical — a palindrome is a palindrome in any language. "onorarono" (9 letters)
# reads the same backwards; solfège "do re mi" is natively Italian.
> onorarono
< That looks like a palindrome.
> do re mi fa
< Those are musical notes (solfège).
# Italian prose must NOT be hijacked. Note "la" alone is a note, but the run is
# not all-notes, so the solfège recognizer correctly declines.
> la lontra nuota nel fiume
< I don't understand that yet.

